    <div class="container">
        <div class="tip">
            <h3>1. Protect Your Personal Information</h3>
            <p>Never share personal information such as your full name, address, phone number, or school name with strangers online.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip">
            <h3>2. Use Strong and Unique Passwords</h3>
            <p>Choose strong passwords for your accounts and avoid using the same password for multiple accounts. Consider using a password manager to keep track of your passwords.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip">
            <h3>3. Be Cautious When Interacting with Others</h3>
            <p>Be wary of people you meet online, as not everyone may have good intentions. Avoid meeting up with strangers in person and report any suspicious behavior to a trusted adult.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip">
            <h3>4. Set Privacy Settings</h3>
            <p>Adjust privacy settings on social media and gaming platforms to control who can see your profile and interact with you online.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tip">
            <h3>5. Think Before You Click</h3>
            <p>Avoid clicking on suspicious links or downloading files from unknown sources, as they may contain malware or phishing attempts.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

